he northwest frontier of India; captured the Indian Ocean islands used as bases by French privateers, notably the Ile de France, now Mauritius; and, in 1811, conquered Java, nominally Dutch but following the incorporation of the Netherlands into the French Empire, effectively French. Besides the details of Lord Minto's career and activities, the book also provides full background information on a wide range of relevant subjects, including the governance and finances of the East India Company,the various polities of the Indian subcontinent and neighbouring regions, and the political situation in Britain and Europe. Amita Das completed her doctorate at the University of Oxford. Aditya Das completed his doctorate at West Virginia University.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aMaritime History. 4aMilitary History. 4aModern History. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Great Britain / General.2bisacsh  aBritish military strategy.  aBritish war history.  aBritish war.  aEuropean politics.  aFrench battle strategy.  aFrench war.  aIndian war.  aNROTC.  aNapoleon Bonaparte.  aROTC.  ahistory of war.  anineteenth century.  apolitical science.  awar strategy.1 aDas, Aditya, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aDas, Aditya, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311143131440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781782048138?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781782048138423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781782048138/original  a978-3-11-143131-4  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles